# DR-BFTOPSIS Simulation Results & Validation

## Corrected Experimental Setup
- **Normal Dataset**: 10 DMs rating 5 alternatives across 4 criteria honestly
- **Biased Dataset**: **Exact copy** of normal, but DM8-DM10 ratings replaced with collusion (A1=max, all others=min)
- **Ground Truth Ranking** (Normal M1): `A2 > A5 > A4 > A1 > A3`

## Final Comparative Results (Biased Dataset)

| Method | Ranking on Biased Data | A1 Position | Match w/ Ground Truth | Status |
|--------|----------------------|-------------|----------------------|--------|
| M1: Normal TOPSIS | A1 > A2 > A5 > A4 > A3 | **#1** | 1/5 | ❌ FAILED |
| M2: Bagged TOPSIS | A1 > A2 > A5 > A4 > A3 | **#1** | 1/5 | ❌ FAILED |
| M3: ML-Filtered | A2 > A5 > A1 > A4 > A3 | **#3** | 3/5 | ✅ NEUTRALIZED |
| M4: Weighted Bagging | A2 > A5 > A1 > A4 > A3 | **#3** | 3/5 | ✅ NEUTRALIZED |
| M5: Cluster-Stratified | A2 > A5 > A4 > A3 > A1 | **#5** | 3/5 | ✅ NEUTRALIZED |
| **M6: Rel-Weighted Agg** | **A2 > A5 > A4 > A1 > A3** | **#4** | **5/5** | ✅ **PERFECT** |

## Key Findings
- **M1 & M2 fail**: Basic TOPSIS and uniform bagging cannot resist a 30% coordinated attack
- **M3 & M4 recover**: ML detects biased DMs (R_k ≈ 0.05 vs honest DMs ≈ 0.5), pushing A1 from #1 → #3
- **M5 goes further**: Excluding the biased cluster entirely pushes A1 to last place (#5)
- **M6 achieves perfect recovery**: Dual-layer reliability weighting produces the **exact same ranking** as the unbiased ground truth (5/5 match)

> [!TIP]
> **M6 is the strongest thesis contribution** — it achieves perfect rank recovery without explicitly removing any DM, purely through mathematical weighting.
